properties.dataChangeRationale: The 1505000759 levee system is located along the left bank of Eagle Creek in Indianapolis, IN. properties.dataChangeRationale:
Incipient overtopping estimated at station 3047.  

This levee is approximately 3,600 feet long on the right bank of of Big Eagle Creek in Indianapolis, IN. Approximately 400 feet of the levee is floodwall that ties into Washington Street. The leveed area was assumed to be bounded by the RR on the south side. properties.name: Williams Ditch Levee Left bank
properties.divisionNames: Great Lakes and Ohio River Division
properties.dataChangeRationale: The alignment was extended west along Williams Ditch to its confluence with Kankakee River. On the east side, the railroad embankment wis included from its junction with the levee north to the bridge at Tully Ditch. Best method for leveed area is Flood Study. Area was terminated along Tully Ditch from the railroad bridge west to Brown Ditch then along Brown Ditch west to Singleton Ditch. From there west along Singleton Ditch until just east of State Line Road at Illinois where another railroad embankment limited flooding northward. The leveed area then follows the railroad west until the flood study polygon ends at the downstream most cross section. To finish the westward flooding, contour 626.18 was used until terminating at a natural division in line with Freedom Road to the south.
